      <guid>/best-practices/spring-boot-structure/</guid>
      <description>CONTEXT This recipe provides details for organizing codebase in a typical spring boot microservice.
SOLUTION Layers Why even have layers today? What year is this?  Most of the examples I see have one Spring bean which does configuration, endpoints, data, security, validation and pancakes&amp;hellip;
 An argument can be made that trivial services (especially focused examples) have no need for the overhead of multiple layers, packages, separation of duties, abstraction, and even basic organization.</description>
